An unemployed man, Justine Abushieye, has been arraigned at a Wuse Zone 2 Senior Magistrates’ Court in Abuja for allegedly stealing a bottle of wine, valued at N18,000. Abushieye, of no fixed address, was arraigned on a one-count charge of theft. Prosecutor Mr. Fidelis Chijioke told the court Yua Timothy, of Jethro Pharmacy, Wuse 2, reported the matter at Wuse Police Station on June 21. He said about 10 am on the same date, Abushieye went to Jethro Pharmacy, Wuse 2, to buy a drug, valued at N100. Chijioke alleged Abushieye, after buying the medicine, stole a bottle of wine, valued at N18,000. He said the offence contravened Section 287 of the Penal Code. Abushieye pleaded not guilty. Magistrate Mrs. Olubunmi Achegbulu granted the accused bail at N50,000 with a surety, who must live in the court’s jurisdiction. She adjourned the case till August 15 for hearing.